subSection.paragraph:
Steroids are a critical source of natural products, which not only act as a pivotal part of membranes to maintain structures, but are also the office of precursors for the synthesis of important substances such as steroid hormones (
Hu et al., 2017
; 
Ohnishi et al., 2009
; 
Qin and Liu, 2004
; 
Sokolov et al., 2019
). Ergosterols are a subclass of steroids, that possess a typical tetracyclic skeleton with an alkyl chain and hydroxyl groups. Apart from classical ergosterols with the mentioned carbon skeleton, rearranged ergosterols have also reported, and some of them have been synthesized, such as dankasterones A and B, resulting from 13 (14 → 8) 
abeo
-frameworks as intermediaries to 
form unprecedented
structures (
Duecker et al., 2020
; 
Taro et al., 1999
). A large number of natural ergosterols have exhibited significant anti-inflammatory (Xiang et al., 2018), anti-tumor (
Lin et al., 2017
), anti-bacterial (
Tanaka et al., 2000
), and neurotrophic activities (
Luo et al., 2017
).

The human hepatocellular carcinoma cell lines, Hep3B, HepG2 and Huh-7 were purchased from Procell Life Technology Co. Ltd. (Wuhan, 
China
), and no evidence of mycoplasma contamination was detected by the PCR-based assay in any of these cell lines. Cells were cultured in Dulbecco’ s modified Eagle’ s medium (DMEM, HyClone, 
USA
) supplemented with 10% FBS (Gibco, 
USA
), 100 
μ
g/ml penicillin and 100 
μ
g/ml streptomycin (Biosharp, 
China
) in an incubator with at 37 
◦
C and a 5% CO 
2
atmosphere. For cell treatment, compounds 
1–13
and sorafenib (MCE, 
USA
), the positive control, were dissolved in DMSO and diluted to specific concentrations with a DMEM complete medium before use. Cell viability and IC 
50
against hepatoma cell lines were tested via a CCK-8 (TOPSCIENCE, 
China
) assay according to the manufacturer’ s instructions. Flow cytometry analysis was performed in a BectonDickinson (BD) FACS Canto II flow cytometer (BD Biosciences, 
USA
) to determine cell cycle progression and apoptosis (Cell Cycle and Apoptosis Analysis Kit, Beyotime, 
China
). The relative distributions of cells in the G0/G1, S, and G2/M phases of the cell cycle were analyzed using Modfit 5.0 software and the rates of apoptotic cells were diagramed by FlowJo V10. For fluorescence microscopy detection of the apoptotic nuclear morphology, cells treated with various substrates were observed via fluorescence microscopy using a fluorescent microscope system (Olympus, 
Japan
) after DAPI staining (Solarbio Life Science, 
China
). GraphPad Prism 6 was used to perform the statistical analyses. For most experiments, two-tailed unpaired t-tests were used to determine statistically significant differences between groups. All experiments were performed at least three times and data are presented as the means ± standard deviation (s.d.) unless otherwise specified.
